  <refnamediv>
    <refname>medianblur</refname>
    <refpurpose>Blurs an image using the median filter.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   inputImage = imread('path of the image')
   outputImg = medianblur(inputImage,ksize)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>inputImage :</term>
      <listitem><para> source image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>ksize :</term>
      <listitem><para>  aperture linear size; it must be odd and greater than 1</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
The function smoothes an image using the median filter with the ksize x ksize aperture.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
inputImage = imread('images/lena.jpg');
ouputImg = medianblur(inputImage,3);
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

